verbose_text: Interestingly, rescue with the ATP5F1D V106G allele corresponding to subject 2 showed more severe phenotypes than rescue with ATP5F1D P82L --the ATP5F1D V106G allele only partially rescued lethality, elicited a glossy-eye phenotype less frequently than ATP5F1D P82 expression, and caused more severe defects in electroretinogram recordings than did the ATP5F1D P82 allele (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
